1
00:00:03,672 --> 00:00:04,640
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:04,640 --> 00:00:06,041
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,041 --> 00:00:07,109
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:08,077 --> 00:00:10,379
I'm saying this loud and clear.

5
00:00:10,379 --> 00:00:11,981
I, Im Ju Hyeong, chose him.

6
00:00:11,981 --> 00:00:13,816
This man is a resident of Yeonri-ri
from now on.

7
00:00:13,816 --> 00:00:14,650
You got that?

8
00:00:14,650 --> 00:00:16,585
Yes.

9
00:00:16,585 --> 00:00:21,757
Seong Tae Hun.

10
00:00:21,757 --> 00:00:24,026
I won't hold back today...

11
00:00:24,493 --> 00:00:26,628
and eat as much as I want.

12
00:00:26,628 --> 00:00:30,499
In that case, I'd better go ahead...

13
00:00:30,499 --> 00:00:33,402
and prepare a feast for everyone.

14
00:00:41,477 --> 00:00:42,511
Big sis.

15
00:00:44,980 --> 00:00:45,848
Big sis.

16
00:00:51,353 --> 00:00:52,321
Thank you...

17
00:00:53,222 --> 00:00:54,456
so much.

18
00:00:57,026 --> 00:00:58,694
If it weren't for that fund,

19
00:00:58,694 --> 00:01:00,663
I don't know what would've happened to me.

20
00:01:00,663 --> 00:01:02,531
- Honey...
- It's fine.

21
00:01:02,531 --> 00:01:04,033
I'm just glad everything's settled now.

22
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,902
Thanks to you, I paid everything back.

23
00:01:06,902 --> 00:01:07,903
Goodness.

24
00:01:07,903 --> 00:01:11,040
But I don't know
how to repay this kindness.

25
00:01:12,374 --> 00:01:16,111
Honestly, I was in agony by myself
without being able to tell my husband.

26
00:01:17,379 --> 00:01:21,083
You saved my whole family.

27
00:01:22,584 --> 00:01:23,752
In that case,

28
00:01:23,752 --> 00:01:27,423
let's just say, as an older sister,
I looked after my younger sister.

29
00:01:29,558 --> 00:01:30,693
Big sis.

30
00:01:31,860 --> 00:01:32,995
Little sis.

31
00:01:34,029 --> 00:01:34,930
Honey.

32
00:01:37,399 --> 00:01:38,267
Honey.

33
00:01:40,269 --> 00:01:41,403
Goodness.

34
00:01:44,173 --> 00:01:45,574
What are you talking about?

35
00:01:46,408 --> 00:01:47,509
What money did you pay back?

36
00:01:51,447 --> 00:01:53,682
Honey, it's not what you think.

37
00:01:53,682 --> 00:01:55,918
What did you help her with?

38
00:01:55,918 --> 00:01:57,853
You see...

39
00:01:59,888 --> 00:02:02,958
Did you get into some kind of trouble?

40
00:02:19,675 --> 00:02:21,043
Explain it to me.

41
00:02:22,211 --> 00:02:24,647
Debt? What is this about?

42
00:02:26,782 --> 00:02:28,450
The moms I borrowed money from...

43
00:02:29,418 --> 00:02:31,220
came here, looking for me.

44
00:02:32,955 --> 00:02:34,089
Why...

45
00:02:34,623 --> 00:02:37,893
didn't you tell me?

46
00:02:39,461 --> 00:02:43,165
You didn't say it was a demotion,

47
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:46,535
but honestly, that's what it looked like.

48
00:02:48,570 --> 00:02:51,307
How could I tell someone
who already sacrificed for the family...

49
00:02:53,008 --> 00:02:56,578
that I lost our kids' tuition too?

50
00:02:57,913 --> 00:03:00,849
Even so, you should've told me!
A village fund?

51
00:03:00,849 --> 00:03:03,152
Do you even know what kind of money
that is? How can you accept it?

52
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:05,721
That...

53
00:03:06,789 --> 00:03:11,360
Ms. Nam gave it to me out of generosity.

54
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,895
She made an excuse to do so.

55
00:03:14,563 --> 00:03:16,432
Why does she need $20,000?

56
00:03:18,434 --> 00:03:19,935
It's my wife's insurance money.

57
00:03:23,739 --> 00:03:26,475
Even so, how could you accept that money?

58
00:03:27,476 --> 00:03:31,246
Ms. Nam put in her own money too.

59
00:03:31,246 --> 00:03:34,616
Is everything solved now
because you paid it back with that money?

60
00:03:34,616 --> 00:03:35,517
Is that so?

61
00:03:35,517 --> 00:03:38,387
Isn't this debt too?
It's an even heavier one.

62
00:03:38,387 --> 00:03:40,122
Now you own them emotionally too.

63
00:03:41,223 --> 00:03:43,192
Yes, I know I was foolish.

64
00:03:45,361 --> 00:03:46,695
But what was I supposed to do?

65
00:03:47,363 --> 00:03:50,499
I had to educate our kids,
but we were always short on money.

66
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:54,603
How was I supposed to know it was a scam?

67
00:04:03,278 --> 00:04:05,948
(MAT STORY)

68
00:04:22,331 --> 00:04:23,232
Mr. Seong.

69
00:04:24,099 --> 00:04:25,901
Your internal loan application
has been approved.

70
00:04:27,303 --> 00:04:29,605
Since it's an internal loan,
the interest rate is relatively low,

71
00:04:30,339 --> 00:04:32,041
but the repayment period
will be quite tight.

72
00:04:32,574 --> 00:04:34,176
What do you mean?

73
00:04:35,277 --> 00:04:37,413
As you can see here,

74
00:04:38,047 --> 00:04:40,616
the full amount must be paid back
before you leave the company.

75
00:04:46,422 --> 00:04:48,757
(Internal Loan Agreement)

76
00:04:49,391 --> 00:04:53,996
(EP 11 At the Edge of a Cliff
To Be Or Not To Be)

77
00:04:53,996 --> 00:04:59,735
(That Is The Question)

78
00:05:05,274 --> 00:05:07,810
(Executive Office)

79
00:05:07,810 --> 00:05:08,744
Come in.

80
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,381
Hey.

81
00:05:13,248 --> 00:05:14,583
Did you call for me, sir?

82
00:05:14,984 --> 00:05:16,785
You're here, Mr. Seong.

83
00:05:17,686 --> 00:05:18,587
Have a seat.

84
00:05:36,705 --> 00:05:39,808
I think it's time you knew.

85
00:05:42,645 --> 00:05:43,879
We're planning...

86
00:05:45,981 --> 00:05:49,284
to build Mat Story's third factory
on the Yeonri-ri site.

87
00:05:53,889 --> 00:05:55,758
A factory?

88
00:05:57,026 --> 00:05:59,561
It'll be a smart factory, so it won't
even need much manpower.

89
00:06:00,229 --> 00:06:02,398
That land in Yeonri-ri...

90
00:06:02,798 --> 00:06:04,133
is the perfect location.

91
00:06:05,467 --> 00:06:09,038
You should produce a harvest
more valuable than cabbage...

92
00:06:09,038 --> 00:06:10,439
with your own hands, Mr. Seong.

93
00:06:11,073 --> 00:06:14,677
The company will help you do your part,
in its own way.

94
00:06:19,181 --> 00:06:20,249
Mr. Seong.

95
00:06:24,086 --> 00:06:25,120
Mr. Seong.

96
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:34,163
No, sir. We can't build a factory
on that land.

97
00:06:34,963 --> 00:06:36,065
What do you mean, we can't?

98
00:06:36,699 --> 00:06:38,334
The people there...

99
00:06:38,334 --> 00:06:41,136
have lived for generations
trusting that land and farming it.

100
00:06:41,470 --> 00:06:44,473
To them, it's not just land.
It's their livelihood, their life.

101
00:06:44,473 --> 00:06:46,709
I've been there and seen it. I know.

102
00:06:46,709 --> 00:06:48,277
If you build a factory there, they will...

103
00:06:48,277 --> 00:06:49,211
Mr. Seong.

104
00:06:51,714 --> 00:06:54,350
I know you care,

105
00:06:55,017 --> 00:06:56,885
but business isn't run on feelings.

106
00:06:58,187 --> 00:06:59,421
More importantly,

107
00:07:06,428 --> 00:07:09,898
the villagers have already
given their consent.

108
00:07:18,807 --> 00:07:21,176
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

109
00:07:22,911 --> 00:07:23,846
Wait.

110
00:07:24,246 --> 00:07:27,683
This is the list
for the free fertilizer distribution.

111
00:07:27,683 --> 00:07:28,684
I personally...

112
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:35,190
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

113
00:07:35,891 --> 00:07:38,060
This can't be.

114
00:07:38,794 --> 00:07:41,196
The title should be...

115
00:07:41,196 --> 00:07:42,631
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

116
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:48,304
Yeonri-ri residents.
Mat Story is giving away...

117
00:07:48,304 --> 00:07:50,005
premium fertilizer for free.

118
00:07:50,005 --> 00:07:52,741
Please sign. Right here.

119
00:07:52,741 --> 00:07:54,443
You know, people's hearts...

120
00:07:55,210 --> 00:07:56,679
It's hard to get past the threshold.

121
00:07:56,679 --> 00:07:59,114
But once you're in, they stop questioning.

122
00:08:00,249 --> 00:08:03,152
And be sure to organize
and submit the residents' list.

123
00:08:03,652 --> 00:08:06,088
(Mat Story Third Factory
Establishment Consent Form)

124
00:08:13,962 --> 00:08:15,631
You did great work.

125
00:08:16,565 --> 00:08:18,600
It isn't easy to go to each villager...

126
00:08:18,934 --> 00:08:20,869
and collect their signatures.

127
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:24,573
Thanks to you, construction will go
very smoothly.

128
00:08:30,779 --> 00:08:32,681
Just stay on my side...

129
00:08:32,681 --> 00:08:35,718
and enjoy the result of this list.

130
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,489
I know how country people are.

131
00:08:42,091 --> 00:08:44,927
They talk about being family
and being one,

132
00:08:48,063 --> 00:08:50,733
but the real family you want to protect...

133
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:52,668
isn't them, right?

134
00:09:06,281 --> 00:09:08,851
There's no issue with the schedule,

135
00:09:08,851 --> 00:09:10,152
so don't worry.

136
00:09:10,986 --> 00:09:12,187
Let's just push it through.

137
00:09:18,627 --> 00:09:19,662
Okay.

138
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:27,703
Why did you report falsified information
to Mr. Bae?

139
00:09:29,471 --> 00:09:30,673
Let's talk later.

140
00:09:32,241 --> 00:09:33,709
What I submitted...

141
00:09:33,709 --> 00:09:36,011
was a list of recipients
for the free fertilizer program.

142
00:09:36,745 --> 00:09:39,048
How did that turn into
a factory consent document...

143
00:09:39,048 --> 00:09:41,016
and get approved?

144
00:09:41,617 --> 00:09:44,687
You were so busy,

145
00:09:44,687 --> 00:09:46,121
so I did it for you.

146
00:09:46,121 --> 00:09:47,856
Business is all about timing.

147
00:09:47,856 --> 00:09:50,326
This is clearly document falsification.

148
00:09:50,893 --> 00:09:53,395
I'm going to correct this.

149
00:09:53,929 --> 00:09:56,565
So what? Are you going to become
a whistleblower?

150
00:09:58,634 --> 00:09:59,902
Well...

151
00:10:00,903 --> 00:10:02,738
There's a long line of people...

152
00:10:02,738 --> 00:10:05,007
who want to take your position.

153
00:10:06,342 --> 00:10:08,510
If you don't like it,
you can always leave.

154
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,279
Why are you getting so worked up?

155
00:10:11,180 --> 00:10:12,281
Is that a threat?

156
00:10:13,549 --> 00:10:14,483
No.

157
00:10:14,850 --> 00:10:16,986
I'm just helping you understand
your place.

158
00:10:20,356 --> 00:10:23,692
I heard you took out
an internal loan today.

159
00:10:27,863 --> 00:10:31,066
You're digging into my personal life now?

160
00:10:32,101 --> 00:10:34,803
Digging? Not at all.
I just happened to find out.

161
00:10:36,405 --> 00:10:38,507
The burden of being
the head of the family.

162
00:10:39,675 --> 00:10:42,544
Watching you struggle like this
just to protect your family...

163
00:10:42,544 --> 00:10:45,014
It almost brings me to tears sometimes.

164
00:10:47,783 --> 00:10:49,018
Let me ask you just one thing.

165
00:10:50,586 --> 00:10:51,920
Why Yeonri-ri?

166
00:10:52,888 --> 00:10:53,756
What?

167
00:10:54,023 --> 00:10:56,592
There are factory sites
all over the country.

168
00:10:56,592 --> 00:10:59,728
So why Simwoo-myeon Yeonri-ri
of all places?

169
00:11:00,529 --> 00:11:01,864
That's...

170
00:11:06,535 --> 00:11:08,971
something the company decides.

171
00:11:09,738 --> 00:11:11,707
Stop asking pointless questions.

172
00:11:11,707 --> 00:11:13,976
The Yeonri-ri seedling
unsuitability report.

173
00:11:13,976 --> 00:11:16,211
Go and sign that.

174
00:11:16,211 --> 00:11:18,814
You're dragging out something
that should've been finished already.

175
00:11:23,619 --> 00:11:25,287
(CEO Kong of Hyeongam Construction)

176
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:30,526
Go.

177
00:11:31,226 --> 00:11:32,961
Go and do your work.

178
00:11:49,745 --> 00:11:53,749
(Yeonri-ri)

179
00:12:14,069 --> 00:12:15,304
Don't just sit there.

180
00:12:16,171 --> 00:12:17,006
Come on.

181
00:12:19,008 --> 00:12:20,542
Come on. Cheers.

182
00:12:21,076 --> 00:12:22,911
He put effort into making this.

183
00:12:22,911 --> 00:12:24,013
Just one sip, Dad.

184
00:12:34,556 --> 00:12:37,259
Mom. Dad. Guess what this is made of.

185
00:12:38,594 --> 00:12:39,495
I don't know.

186
00:12:39,895 --> 00:12:40,929
Black raspberry?

187
00:12:42,931 --> 00:12:43,899
Omija berries.

188
00:12:46,201 --> 00:12:47,269
Ta da.

189
00:12:47,736 --> 00:12:49,905
This is omija?

190
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,441
You couldn't tell, right?

191
00:12:52,441 --> 00:12:54,343
Ji Cheon made it using a special recipe.

192
00:12:56,512 --> 00:12:59,648
It's called omija because it has
five different flavors.

193
00:13:00,249 --> 00:13:03,185
Sweet, bitter, sour, spicy, and salty.

194
00:13:03,919 --> 00:13:06,388
I tasted omija for the first time
in Yeonri-ri.

195
00:13:06,989 --> 00:13:09,591
It might sound presumptuous,

196
00:13:10,125 --> 00:13:11,226
but the taste is just like life.

197
00:13:12,161 --> 00:13:13,962
Goodness.

198
00:13:15,297 --> 00:13:18,233
Joy, anger, sorrow, and happiness
are all over the place, just like life.

199
00:13:18,934 --> 00:13:20,202
From those flavors,

200
00:13:20,602 --> 00:13:23,505
I focused on the sweet, bitter,
and sour taste...

201
00:13:23,505 --> 00:13:24,673
to make this omija mojito.

202
00:13:25,107 --> 00:13:26,842
Omija mojito.

203
00:13:27,343 --> 00:13:28,811
Wow.

204
00:13:28,811 --> 00:13:29,678
Yes.

205
00:13:32,081 --> 00:13:33,048
It's the taste of life.

206
00:13:34,984 --> 00:13:36,719
It's medicine.

207
00:13:36,719 --> 00:13:38,153
This is amazing.

208
00:13:38,854 --> 00:13:40,389
Cheers.

209
00:13:40,389 --> 00:13:42,324
- Okay.
- Everybody, cheers.

210
00:13:42,624 --> 00:13:44,293
Cheers.

211
00:13:54,203 --> 00:13:55,137
Ji Cheon.

212
00:13:55,671 --> 00:13:56,739
You...

213
00:13:56,739 --> 00:13:59,708
That omija mojito was really good.

214
00:13:59,708 --> 00:14:01,043
In the future,

215
00:14:01,043 --> 00:14:03,345
even if someone comes and tries...

216
00:14:03,345 --> 00:14:06,148
to sweet-talk you
into giving them the recipe,

217
00:14:06,382 --> 00:14:07,650
don't give it to them.

218
00:14:09,418 --> 00:14:10,319
Let's go.

219
00:14:10,319 --> 00:14:12,421
Definitely don't give it to people
like that.

220
00:14:14,723 --> 00:14:17,326
It's Seong Tae Hun.

221
00:14:17,326 --> 00:14:19,395
Look. It's our hero, Seong Tae Hun.

222
00:14:19,395 --> 00:14:20,629
Thanks to you,

223
00:14:20,629 --> 00:14:23,599
the people of Yeonri-ri
can finally sleep peacefully.

224
00:14:23,599 --> 00:14:27,569
So we prepared an appreciation plaque.

225
00:14:27,569 --> 00:14:30,272
But that foolish Wang Dong Sik
didn't bring it.

226
00:14:30,272 --> 00:14:32,741
So I'll get it myself tomorrow...

227
00:14:32,741 --> 00:14:33,976
and give it to you.

228
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:35,811
I don't need a plaque.

229
00:14:35,811 --> 00:14:38,614
What do you mean?
You should accept it, of course.

230
00:14:39,048 --> 00:14:40,749
The father helps out with work,

231
00:14:40,749 --> 00:14:42,451
and the son helps out with his drink.

232
00:14:42,451 --> 00:14:44,420
Mr. Seong and Seong Ji Cheon.

233
00:14:44,420 --> 00:14:46,221
May you become rich.

234
00:14:47,156 --> 00:14:50,592
That omija thing.
What was it called again?

235
00:14:50,592 --> 00:14:52,061
- Mojito.
- Maldives?

236
00:14:52,061 --> 00:14:54,096
Have you tried that omija mojito?

237
00:14:54,096 --> 00:14:56,198
It's incredible. You should make him one.

238
00:14:56,732 --> 00:14:59,435
It's sweet and delicious.

239
00:15:00,369 --> 00:15:01,971
You should take your father home.

240
00:15:01,971 --> 00:15:03,605
Are you treating me like I'm drunk?

241
00:15:03,605 --> 00:15:04,707
I'm not drunk.

242
00:15:04,974 --> 00:15:06,842
You're trying to send me home.

243
00:15:06,842 --> 00:15:08,944
Let's see. Where's my house again?

244
00:15:08,944 --> 00:15:11,347
Look. I'm going home.

245
00:15:13,449 --> 00:15:15,250
Omija...

246
00:15:27,229 --> 00:15:28,797
I'm saying this loud and clear.

247
00:15:28,797 --> 00:15:30,666
This man is a resident of Yeonri-ri
from now on.

248
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:31,533
You got that?

249
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:33,335
Yes.

250
00:15:33,335 --> 00:15:37,806
Seong Tae Hun.

251
00:15:40,442 --> 00:15:42,044
We're planning...

252
00:15:43,045 --> 00:15:45,781
to build Mat Story's third factory
on the Yeonri-ri site.

253
00:15:59,361 --> 00:16:05,234
(Wang Dong Hardware)

254
00:16:06,568 --> 00:16:07,703
It's dazzling.

255
00:16:08,337 --> 00:16:10,706
Look at that shine. It's great.

256
00:16:10,939 --> 00:16:12,141
Look at that edge. It could cut me.

257
00:16:12,141 --> 00:16:13,075
That's sharp!

258
00:16:14,943 --> 00:16:16,278
You're here.

259
00:16:16,278 --> 00:16:17,813
- Are you finished?
- Yes.

260
00:16:17,813 --> 00:16:19,682
- Is it done? Let me see.
- Take a look.

261
00:16:21,016 --> 00:16:23,952
The appreciation plaque. Seong Tae Hun.
It's awesome.

262
00:16:23,952 --> 00:16:24,787
It's great.

263
00:16:24,787 --> 00:16:26,255
I, the village chief, should present it.

264
00:16:26,255 --> 00:16:27,323
Yes, of course.

265
00:16:28,090 --> 00:16:29,391
But I saw him on the way to work.

266
00:16:29,391 --> 00:16:31,293
It looked like Mr. Seong
was headed somewhere.

267
00:16:31,293 --> 00:16:34,296
You know the livestock shed
past the field over there?

268
00:16:35,230 --> 00:16:36,165
The livestock shed?

269
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:40,536
I'm doing what I was told.

270
00:16:59,922 --> 00:17:02,558
What are you doing here?

271
00:17:04,059 --> 00:17:07,062
Was it from the time you were assigned
to the Yeonri-ri branch?

272
00:17:08,063 --> 00:17:09,531
That you got on the same boat as Mr. Choi.

273
00:17:12,434 --> 00:17:13,969
You told me...

274
00:17:14,303 --> 00:17:15,738
that I'm just like you.

275
00:17:16,639 --> 00:17:19,308
I finally understand what you meant.

276
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:24,680
A situation where you bite the bait
thrown by someone like Mr. Choi...

277
00:17:25,681 --> 00:17:27,816
and end up making others
cry tears of blood.

278
00:17:28,684 --> 00:17:30,219
That's what you were trying to say, right?

279
00:17:31,687 --> 00:17:33,856
Tell me! Why Yeonri-ri?

280
00:17:37,059 --> 00:17:38,227
Mr. Choi didn't see...

281
00:17:39,795 --> 00:17:42,031
this land as farmland from the beginning.

282
00:17:43,298 --> 00:17:45,301
He probably had another use
for it in mind.

283
00:17:46,101 --> 00:17:48,337
Another use?

284
00:17:49,271 --> 00:17:50,506
What's this?

285
00:17:51,307 --> 00:17:53,442
I didn't know there was a place like this.

286
00:17:55,010 --> 00:17:56,011
It's a nice setup.

287
00:17:56,011 --> 00:17:57,346
Are you in there, Tae Hun?

288
00:17:58,314 --> 00:17:59,348
What is this place?

289
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:01,984
Are you in there, Tae Hun?

290
00:18:03,185 --> 00:18:04,253
There you are.

291
00:18:04,853 --> 00:18:05,854
Your plaque is ready.

292
00:18:06,922 --> 00:18:09,291
Hello. Let me...

293
00:18:09,291 --> 00:18:11,727
Let me say hello.
I don't think we've properly met.

294
00:18:18,901 --> 00:18:20,903
What are you doing here?

295
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:23,138
How dare you!

296
00:18:23,839 --> 00:18:24,840
Calm down.

297
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,508
Calm down and let's talk.

298
00:18:26,508 --> 00:18:27,643
Let go.

299
00:18:27,643 --> 00:18:30,346
Do you even know what he did to Yeonri-ri?

300
00:18:30,346 --> 00:18:31,246
Hey.

301
00:18:46,428 --> 00:18:47,496
Wait.

302
00:18:47,896 --> 00:18:50,165
Wait.

303
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:52,034
So...

304
00:18:52,267 --> 00:18:54,036
what do you mean
you won't pay for the cabbage?

305
00:18:54,036 --> 00:18:55,738
(Ten years ago)

306
00:18:55,738 --> 00:18:58,474
How dare you bring us
cabbage contaminated with chemicals?

307
00:18:59,475 --> 00:19:02,778
They found an excessive amount
of pesticide.

308
00:19:02,778 --> 00:19:03,712
How dare you.

309
00:19:04,179 --> 00:19:06,215
That can't be true.

310
00:19:06,215 --> 00:19:09,184
Our cabbage was grown
only with eco-friendly pesticides!

311
00:19:12,655 --> 00:19:13,455
Let's go.

312
00:19:13,822 --> 00:19:16,792
No, please. You can't leave like this.

313
00:19:17,726 --> 00:19:19,361
Please help us.

314
00:19:19,361 --> 00:19:22,131
Everyone in our village depends
on this land to survive.

315
00:19:22,131 --> 00:19:24,566
Please help us. Please save us.

316
00:19:24,566 --> 00:19:25,467
Please?

317
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:27,102
Don't touch me with those filthy hands.

318
00:19:28,137 --> 00:19:29,972
Come on.

319
00:19:33,309 --> 00:19:35,511
This is a breach of contract, okay?

320
00:19:36,111 --> 00:19:39,248
Just be glad we're not charging penalties.

321
00:19:39,715 --> 00:19:41,116
How dare you.

322
00:19:53,429 --> 00:19:54,396
You...

323
00:19:55,197 --> 00:19:56,632
Are you even human?

324
00:20:02,371 --> 00:20:05,074
Didn't you tell us to trust you?

325
00:20:05,407 --> 00:20:07,576
When I was the youth leader,

326
00:20:07,576 --> 00:20:08,877
they came with a business proposal.

327
00:20:09,378 --> 00:20:12,081
They said they'd turn Yeonri-ri
into a cabbage specialty region,

328
00:20:12,081 --> 00:20:13,349
talking about mutual growth.

329
00:20:16,785 --> 00:20:18,887
Do you know what Mat Story did...

330
00:20:18,887 --> 00:20:20,522
with the cabbage our people worked
so hard to grow?

331
00:20:22,725 --> 00:20:25,894
Our Yeonri-ri cabbage is clean.

332
00:20:26,862 --> 00:20:29,098
We raised each cabbage...

333
00:20:29,098 --> 00:20:30,933
like we were raising our own children.

334
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:34,169
Do you know how much care went into
growing each and every cabbage?

335
00:20:34,803 --> 00:20:36,672
Please hear us out.

336
00:20:36,672 --> 00:20:38,007
Our Yeonri-ri cabbage...

337
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:41,944
Please let it be inspected again.

338
00:20:41,944 --> 00:20:43,812
Please inspect it once more.

339
00:20:44,079 --> 00:20:46,181
You shouldn't do this to other people.

340
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:51,420
(Mat Story deceived
the farmers of Yeonri-ri)

341
00:20:52,221 --> 00:20:54,323
Do you know how many people
left the village after that?

342
00:20:55,891 --> 00:20:57,459
My family ended up buried in debt too.

343
00:20:59,028 --> 00:21:01,063
Now do you understand
why I hate Mat Story so much?

344
00:21:01,830 --> 00:21:03,932
I just want to die
when I think about that time.

345
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:10,439
I had no idea about that.

346
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:15,778
But Tae Hun...

347
00:21:16,312 --> 00:21:17,579
I trust you.

348
00:21:26,455 --> 00:21:27,456
Goodness.

349
00:21:40,903 --> 00:21:43,572
(Appreciation Plaque, Seong Tae Hun)

350
00:21:56,118 --> 00:21:58,988
([Deposit] $30,000 Mat Story)

351
00:22:12,868 --> 00:22:13,869
Honey.

352
00:22:15,771 --> 00:22:16,805
What's wrong?

353
00:22:17,539 --> 00:22:19,174
Did something happen today?

354
00:22:23,512 --> 00:22:24,380
You...

355
00:22:25,547 --> 00:22:28,150
felt quite frustrated that I stayed...

356
00:22:29,251 --> 00:22:30,686
in the same position for years, right?

357
00:22:37,059 --> 00:22:38,761
I'd be lying...

358
00:22:40,396 --> 00:22:41,664
if I said I never did.

359
00:22:43,932 --> 00:22:46,335
You only focused on research,

360
00:22:47,603 --> 00:22:51,173
and you were never good
at pleasing your superiors.

361
00:22:55,577 --> 00:22:59,515
But that's who you are. What can I do?

362
00:23:04,987 --> 00:23:06,155
If I...

363
00:23:09,692 --> 00:23:11,660
had been like them,

364
00:23:13,595 --> 00:23:15,230
doing whatever it takes to climb up,

365
00:23:16,565 --> 00:23:19,735
would our lives be different now?

366
00:23:25,607 --> 00:23:26,842
Why would you think about that...

367
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:29,812
out of the blue?

368
00:23:31,613 --> 00:23:32,648
I've just...

369
00:23:35,818 --> 00:23:36,919
had a lot...

370
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:39,621
on my mind lately.

371
00:23:54,169 --> 00:23:55,070
Mom.

372
00:23:55,437 --> 00:23:56,372
Yes?

373
00:23:58,507 --> 00:23:59,375
Goodness.

374
00:24:01,777 --> 00:24:05,581
This is my friend. Her name is Han Wu Ju.

375
00:24:05,981 --> 00:24:07,282
Hello.

376
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:09,118
I see.

377
00:24:10,085 --> 00:24:12,054
Hi.

378
00:24:13,622 --> 00:24:16,291
I was told never to visit
a friend's house empty-handed.

379
00:24:17,026 --> 00:24:19,528
My dad told me to bring this.

380
00:24:20,162 --> 00:24:22,197
This Yakdol pork is really good.

381
00:24:22,831 --> 00:24:25,601
I've heard...

382
00:24:25,601 --> 00:24:27,469
this is really good.

383
00:24:29,271 --> 00:24:31,006
It's also good for your health.

384
00:24:31,006 --> 00:24:33,776
He said it'll taste even better
if everyone eats it together.

385
00:24:34,643 --> 00:24:37,379
Give me a little time.
I'll grill it for you right away.

386
00:24:37,379 --> 00:24:38,213
Okay.

387
00:24:38,614 --> 00:24:39,948
- Let's go.
- Okay.

388
00:24:41,517 --> 00:24:43,285
Do you want to see my pea plant?

389
00:24:43,285 --> 00:24:44,753
It's grown more since last time.

390
00:24:44,753 --> 00:24:46,588
That? Yes.

391
00:24:53,395 --> 00:24:56,465
Ji Sang, you read some pretty hard books.

392
00:24:58,367 --> 00:25:01,103
I read them in Canada.

393
00:25:01,103 --> 00:25:02,471
Really?

394
00:25:02,471 --> 00:25:04,173
Ji Sang, those are all my...

395
00:25:04,173 --> 00:25:05,841
You got something in your mouth.

396
00:25:07,343 --> 00:25:09,611
If there's any book you want to read,
you can take it.

397
00:25:14,116 --> 00:25:15,884
Your little brother is so cute.

398
00:25:16,585 --> 00:25:17,953
Your name is Ji Gu, right?

399
00:25:17,953 --> 00:25:18,887
Yes.

400
00:25:18,887 --> 00:25:22,358
Is Ji Sang your first boyfriend?

401
00:25:24,893 --> 00:25:26,428
I...

402
00:25:26,428 --> 00:25:29,531
When Ji Sang was in Canada, Carol...

403
00:25:30,132 --> 00:25:31,533
Mom.

404
00:25:31,533 --> 00:25:34,803
Mom, that Dol pork...

405
00:25:35,437 --> 00:25:36,772
It's Yakdol pork.

406
00:25:37,406 --> 00:25:40,876
There's plenty,

407
00:25:41,310 --> 00:25:42,978
so eat up.

408
00:25:43,679 --> 00:25:45,781
Enjoy your time here, Wu Ju.

409
00:25:47,316 --> 00:25:49,251
Look after Ji Gu, okay?

410
00:25:50,352 --> 00:25:52,421
I'm going out for a bit.

411
00:25:56,158 --> 00:25:57,126
Okay, Mother.

412
00:25:57,693 --> 00:25:59,895
I'll look after my brother.

413
00:25:59,895 --> 00:26:02,398
Don't worry and be safe.

414
00:26:02,398 --> 00:26:03,732
Okay.

415
00:26:10,406 --> 00:26:11,307
It's good.

416
00:26:18,514 --> 00:26:20,115
Try some kimbap too.

417
00:26:29,024 --> 00:26:30,559
My goodness.

418
00:26:32,161 --> 00:26:34,697
I told you to take your time
paying it back.

419
00:26:35,564 --> 00:26:37,199
Why did you pay it back so quickly?

420
00:26:38,233 --> 00:26:41,637
My husband was able to get a loan
from his company.

421
00:26:42,271 --> 00:26:43,772
Thank you so much.

422
00:26:45,808 --> 00:26:47,343
I'm glad it all worked out.

423
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:51,947
But Mr. Seong is going to have to work
even harder now.

424
00:26:53,716 --> 00:26:54,750
I know.

425
00:26:57,553 --> 00:27:01,557
My husband ended up
carrying an even heavier burden.

426
00:27:06,295 --> 00:27:08,831
A married couple is one body.

427
00:27:09,398 --> 00:27:11,667
When things get tough for him later,

428
00:27:12,067 --> 00:27:14,036
you can do the same for him.

429
00:27:23,145 --> 00:27:24,246
I'm home, honey.

430
00:27:34,523 --> 00:27:36,091
What are you doing in the kitchen
at this hour?

431
00:27:36,992 --> 00:27:38,494
And what happened to your hands?

432
00:27:39,828 --> 00:27:41,196
I was practicing using a knife.

433
00:27:42,264 --> 00:27:43,198
A knife?

434
00:27:44,667 --> 00:27:45,901
You told me yourself.

435
00:27:46,669 --> 00:27:48,904
Choices come with responsibility.

436
00:27:52,708 --> 00:27:53,642
I...

437
00:27:55,110 --> 00:27:58,614
want to properly learn how to cook.

438
00:27:59,782 --> 00:28:00,616
Cook?

439
00:28:02,284 --> 00:28:03,852
A knife used to cut a human body...

440
00:28:05,087 --> 00:28:07,356
was always so terrifying to me.

441
00:28:09,291 --> 00:28:10,225
But...

442
00:28:12,428 --> 00:28:13,696
when it's used for cooking,

443
00:28:15,030 --> 00:28:16,065
a knife is kind.

444
00:28:18,267 --> 00:28:19,134
You've...

445
00:28:20,202 --> 00:28:21,337
found your path.

446
00:28:24,807 --> 00:28:26,008
Thanks, Dad.

447
00:28:27,609 --> 00:28:29,478
Even when I decided to drop out on my own,

448
00:28:31,413 --> 00:28:33,415
even when Mom left because of me,

449
00:28:33,415 --> 00:28:34,683
you trusted me and waited.

450
00:28:37,553 --> 00:28:40,756
I will do my best in life as your son.

451
00:28:58,307 --> 00:28:59,575
Hi, Mr. Jeong.

452
00:28:59,808 --> 00:29:02,111
Mr. Seong. I'm going to Yeonri-ri
tomorrow on a business trip.

453
00:29:03,912 --> 00:29:05,914
This soon?

454
00:29:06,515 --> 00:29:09,918
Mr. Choi said there's no time to delay
and told me to hurry.

455
00:29:09,918 --> 00:29:11,954
He said that if you're busy,

456
00:29:11,954 --> 00:29:13,389
I should get it started myself.

457
00:29:14,089 --> 00:29:15,457
I'll see you tomorrow.

458
00:29:23,799 --> 00:29:25,467
There's a long line of people...

459
00:29:25,701 --> 00:29:27,936
who want to take your position.

460
00:29:28,637 --> 00:29:31,106
I heard you took out
an internal loan today.

461
00:29:32,341 --> 00:29:34,977
The full amount must be paid back
before you leave the company.

462
00:29:35,344 --> 00:29:37,313
(Deposit $30,000 Mat Story)

463
00:29:39,415 --> 00:29:42,184
I know how country people are.

464
00:29:44,586 --> 00:29:46,088
That's how it is in Yeonri-ri.

465
00:29:46,789 --> 00:29:48,791
They live with their lives laid bare
like this,

466
00:29:48,791 --> 00:29:51,126
so how could I possibly turn
my back on them?

467
00:29:53,495 --> 00:29:54,430
Here.

468
00:29:55,264 --> 00:29:56,465
The same goes for you now.

469
00:29:57,766 --> 00:29:59,101
Now that you've eaten this food,

470
00:30:00,369 --> 00:30:03,439
you've taken a piece of everyone
in Yeonri-ri.

471
00:30:03,439 --> 00:30:04,373
You got that?

472
00:30:06,108 --> 00:30:07,810
I'm saying this loud and clear.

473
00:30:07,810 --> 00:30:10,212
This man is a resident of Yeonri-ri
from now on.

474
00:30:10,212 --> 00:30:11,113
You got that?

475
00:30:11,113 --> 00:30:15,117
Seong Tae Hun.

476
00:30:16,785 --> 00:30:20,055
They talk about being family
and being one,

477
00:30:20,055 --> 00:30:22,591
but the real family you want to protect...

478
00:30:23,459 --> 00:30:24,493
isn't them, right?

479
00:30:25,127 --> 00:30:27,529
I don't care what I go through.

480
00:30:27,529 --> 00:30:29,031
I can endure anything.

481
00:30:29,765 --> 00:30:31,266
But not my family.

482
00:30:31,266 --> 00:30:32,668
It's okay.

483
00:30:32,668 --> 00:30:34,703
I will get through this no matter what
and go back.

484
00:30:35,137 --> 00:30:37,239
Back to my position at Mat Story in Seoul.

485
00:30:39,174 --> 00:30:42,811
In my life, there is no such word
as giving up.

486
00:30:42,811 --> 00:30:45,247
You three and my cabbages.

487
00:31:20,849 --> 00:31:23,819
Come out and eat breakfast, kids.

488
00:31:24,219 --> 00:31:25,654
Cheon, Sang, and Gu.

489
00:31:26,689 --> 00:31:27,623
Come and eat.

490
00:31:33,095 --> 00:31:34,096
What's going on, honey?

491
00:31:34,930 --> 00:31:36,498
You just came back from headquarters.

492
00:31:37,466 --> 00:31:38,901
Are you going somewhere again today?

493
00:31:38,901 --> 00:31:40,402
Mr. Jeong is coming here today.

494
00:31:41,103 --> 00:31:41,937
I'll be back later.

495
00:31:42,705 --> 00:31:43,639
Okay.

496
00:31:43,639 --> 00:31:46,308
Honey. Eat breakfast before you go.

497
00:31:47,076 --> 00:31:48,377
You're leaving without eating?

498
00:31:53,816 --> 00:31:56,151
(Cafe Sunny)

499
00:31:56,151 --> 00:31:57,353
Where's the powder?

500
00:31:58,687 --> 00:32:00,322
Kids, where are you off to?

501
00:32:03,492 --> 00:32:06,895
A workshop for menu development.

502
00:32:07,529 --> 00:32:08,497
A date?

503
00:32:08,497 --> 00:32:09,798
No. It really is a workshop.

504
00:32:10,866 --> 00:32:12,334
Anyway, we'll be back later.

505
00:32:12,334 --> 00:32:13,435
Goodbye, boss.

506
00:32:13,435 --> 00:32:15,137
All right. Have a good time.

507
00:32:17,806 --> 00:32:19,408
They are dating each other, right?

508
00:32:20,542 --> 00:32:21,644
Are you going to let them?

509
00:32:22,645 --> 00:32:24,847
They said it's a workshop.

510
00:32:24,847 --> 00:32:27,182
Sure. You're so naive.

511
00:32:28,784 --> 00:32:30,653
She's smiling with joy.

512
00:32:38,761 --> 00:32:40,796
- Hello.
- Welcome.

513
00:32:41,430 --> 00:32:43,132
There are so many pretty things.

514
00:32:44,099 --> 00:32:45,434
This is so pretty.

515
00:32:46,635 --> 00:32:48,170
This would totally suit you, Bo Mi.

516
00:32:49,538 --> 00:32:50,539
It sparkles,

517
00:32:51,273 --> 00:32:52,274
like you.

518
00:32:55,711 --> 00:32:56,912
Let's try it on.

519
00:33:04,353 --> 00:33:05,487
It's my gift to you.

520
00:33:05,487 --> 00:33:06,922
What? For real?

521
00:33:08,957 --> 00:33:11,393
Wow. It's so pretty.

522
00:33:14,463 --> 00:33:15,597
Try one on too, Ji Cheon.

523
00:33:15,998 --> 00:33:17,700
Me? Why would I?

524
00:33:17,700 --> 00:33:20,202
If it suits you, we can wear them
as matching bracelets.

525
00:33:20,202 --> 00:33:22,037
It looks better on you.

526
00:33:22,037 --> 00:33:23,973
I know. But...

527
00:33:23,973 --> 00:33:25,474
if it looks good on you,
we can both wear it as a couple.

528
00:33:25,474 --> 00:33:26,642
Matching bracelets.

529
00:33:26,642 --> 00:33:28,143
I can't wear things like this.

530
00:33:28,143 --> 00:33:29,678
Why not? Just try it.

531
00:33:29,678 --> 00:33:30,646
- Just once.
- No.

532
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:32,748
Why not? Just once.

533
00:33:32,748 --> 00:33:34,183
Just once.

534
00:33:34,183 --> 00:33:36,685
Just once.

535
00:33:48,097 --> 00:33:50,466
- Something smells fishy.
- Fishy?

536
00:33:50,466 --> 00:33:53,802
- Your cutie is here, Hye Sun.
- Hello.

537
00:33:54,470 --> 00:33:57,106
Where's the light bulb?
You didn't bring it?

538
00:33:57,106 --> 00:33:58,540
Dong Sik will bring it.

539
00:33:58,540 --> 00:34:00,609
Are they playing hooky already?

540
00:34:00,609 --> 00:34:03,712
Bo Mi took him away.

541
00:34:03,712 --> 00:34:04,713
What? Just the two of them?

542
00:34:04,980 --> 00:34:08,317
Maybe you should be looking
for a wedding hall already.

543
00:34:09,218 --> 00:34:10,886
No, they're just kids.

544
00:34:10,886 --> 00:34:13,422
- No, I can't let her get married.
- Goodness.

545
00:34:13,422 --> 00:34:17,493
You were calling out his name
with love the other day.

546
00:34:17,493 --> 00:34:19,862
Your eyes were smitten with love.

547
00:34:21,397 --> 00:34:23,966
Emergency! This is a huge problem!

548
00:34:25,601 --> 00:34:28,070
- Emergency!
- What's wrong with him?

549
00:34:28,070 --> 00:34:28,871
What is it?

550
00:34:28,871 --> 00:34:29,772
Where's the light bulb?

551
00:34:29,772 --> 00:34:31,340
That's not the issue right now.

552
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:32,775
- Didn't you see the news?
- The news?

553
00:34:32,775 --> 00:34:34,643
What? Some idol's dating scandal
or something?

554
00:34:34,643 --> 00:34:35,611
No.

555
00:34:36,645 --> 00:34:38,147
They're building...

556
00:34:38,147 --> 00:34:40,115
a Mat Story factory in Yeonri-ri.

557
00:34:40,115 --> 00:34:41,984
In Yeonri-ri?

558
00:34:41,984 --> 00:34:43,085
- A factory?
- Yes.

559
00:34:43,085 --> 00:34:44,553
Take a look at this.

560
00:34:44,553 --> 00:34:45,421
What?

561
00:34:45,888 --> 00:34:47,790
Simwoo-myeon Yeonri-ri...

562
00:34:47,790 --> 00:34:51,160
is selected as the site
for Mat Story's third factory?

563
00:34:52,961 --> 00:34:53,896
My goodness.

564
00:34:54,930 --> 00:34:57,032
Then what happens to all the farmland?

565
00:34:58,434 --> 00:35:00,402
How can they build a factory here?

566
00:35:01,070 --> 00:35:02,638
- Hey.
- Chief.

567
00:35:02,638 --> 00:35:03,672
Where are you going?

568
00:35:04,239 --> 00:35:05,207
Wait.

569
00:35:11,647 --> 00:35:14,116
I've put together
a full list of landowners.

570
00:35:15,050 --> 00:35:16,318
But Mr. Seong...

571
00:35:16,318 --> 00:35:19,355
I heard you've grown quite attached
to the residents here.

572
00:35:19,355 --> 00:35:20,923
It won't be easy convincing them
to sell, right?

573
00:35:25,661 --> 00:35:27,529
(List of Landowners
in Mat Story Third Factory Site)

574
00:35:32,001 --> 00:35:32,768
(Kang Sang Jin)

575
00:35:32,768 --> 00:35:34,637
This is livestock land.

576
00:35:34,637 --> 00:35:36,739
But he's the only one
who's not from this village.

577
00:35:36,739 --> 00:35:38,007
That land?

578
00:35:38,307 --> 00:35:40,376
The ownership changed about ten years ago.

579
00:35:40,976 --> 00:35:42,978
Did you set up a separate meeting
with him?

580
00:35:43,479 --> 00:35:44,546
Not yet.

581
00:35:44,847 --> 00:35:48,183
I was planning to contact
the current residents of Yeonri-ri first.

582
00:35:49,118 --> 00:35:49,985
I'll do it.

583
00:35:53,022 --> 00:35:54,957
What are you talking about
out of the blue?

584
00:35:54,957 --> 00:35:57,493
Are you telling me to sell this land?

585
00:35:57,926 --> 00:35:59,361
The company has already set...

586
00:35:59,361 --> 00:36:01,697
compensation guidelines.

587
00:36:02,297 --> 00:36:05,234
Cooperating will be in your best interest.

588
00:36:06,235 --> 00:36:07,536
He's right, sir.

589
00:36:07,536 --> 00:36:10,673
Up to this point will be part of
the factory site development.

590
00:36:10,673 --> 00:36:12,107
You see this here?

591
00:36:12,107 --> 00:36:14,843
If you look here, from here...

592
00:36:16,312 --> 00:36:18,247
There he is. Goodness.

593
00:36:20,916 --> 00:36:22,618
Mr. Seong.

594
00:36:24,386 --> 00:36:25,387
Seong Tae Hun.

595
00:36:26,055 --> 00:36:28,424
Why aren't you answering your phone?

596
00:36:29,325 --> 00:36:30,459
Goodness.

597
00:36:30,993 --> 00:36:33,195
I saw a weird article.

598
00:36:33,195 --> 00:36:36,932
It says Mat Story is building
a factory here.

599
00:36:36,932 --> 00:36:38,000
How ridiculous.

600
00:36:46,241 --> 00:36:48,544
If you've seen the article,
then it'll be easier to explain.

601
00:36:48,544 --> 00:36:51,080
That's what's going to happen.

602
00:36:53,449 --> 00:36:55,517
You think this is some kind of a joke?

603
00:36:55,517 --> 00:36:56,852
What in the world are you talking about?

604
00:36:57,453 --> 00:37:00,923
We'll begin the land acquisition process
starting today.

605
00:37:00,923 --> 00:37:04,193
Please cooperate in persuading
the villagers.

606
00:37:07,796 --> 00:37:09,064
Is something wrong?

607
00:37:09,298 --> 00:37:11,300
Is the company forcing you to do this?

608
00:37:11,967 --> 00:37:13,769
It was Noh Hyeon Gap, wasn't it?

609
00:37:13,769 --> 00:37:15,971
You've been like this ever since
you met that jerk.

610
00:37:16,271 --> 00:37:17,973
Does he have something on you?

611
00:37:20,376 --> 00:37:22,311
I'll go talk to him. Wait here.

612
00:37:22,311 --> 00:37:23,846
Stay right here.

613
00:37:27,449 --> 00:37:29,251
If the village chief's reacting like that,

614
00:37:29,251 --> 00:37:31,320
cooperation might be difficult
moving forward.

615
00:37:32,021 --> 00:37:32,855
Let's go.

616
00:37:33,789 --> 00:37:36,058
You're not going to wait for the chief?

617
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,328
Please cooperate with us.

618
00:37:53,375 --> 00:37:55,711
Noh Hyeon Gap.

619
00:37:56,445 --> 00:37:58,080
You jerk. You're here, aren't you?

620
00:37:58,747 --> 00:37:59,648
Noh Hyeon Gap.

621
00:38:00,282 --> 00:38:02,418
You.

622
00:38:02,418 --> 00:38:04,119
What did you say to Seong Tae Hun?

623
00:38:05,387 --> 00:38:08,223
What did you say to turn that bear
into a snake?

624
00:38:09,058 --> 00:38:09,992
What did you say to him?

625
00:38:11,627 --> 00:38:12,528
Tell me.

626
00:38:14,363 --> 00:38:15,931
Should we end this once and for all?

627
00:38:19,068 --> 00:38:21,437
You got something, don't you?

628
00:38:22,838 --> 00:38:24,740
Unbelievable.

629
00:38:24,740 --> 00:38:27,042
This is that document from ten years ago.

630
00:38:27,042 --> 00:38:28,577
What are you up to?

631
00:38:29,478 --> 00:38:33,215
They found an excessive amount
of pesticide.

632
00:38:33,782 --> 00:38:34,717
How dare you.

633
00:38:38,988 --> 00:38:40,189
(Analysis Report)

634
00:38:42,524 --> 00:38:45,327
(Written by Seong Tae Hun)

635
00:39:02,177 --> 00:39:04,313
We were completely fooled.

636
00:39:04,313 --> 00:39:07,583
That report from ten years ago...

637
00:39:07,583 --> 00:39:10,352
The one that ruined our cabbage
saying it was contaminated...

638
00:39:10,352 --> 00:39:12,955
The one who wrote that piece of paper...

639
00:39:13,489 --> 00:39:14,690
was Seong Tae Hun.

640
00:39:16,125 --> 00:39:17,426
Are you serious?

641
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,228
There's no way.

642
00:39:19,228 --> 00:39:20,496
I checked it myself.

643
00:39:21,363 --> 00:39:23,866
He came to us pretending not to know,

644
00:39:23,866 --> 00:39:26,468
gained our trust, and waited
for the right moment to betray us.

645
00:39:27,670 --> 00:39:28,737
Unbelievable.

646
00:39:29,438 --> 00:39:30,539
Everyone.

647
00:39:30,539 --> 00:39:34,009
They can never build a factory here, okay?

648
00:39:34,009 --> 00:39:37,212
- Okay.
- Of course not.

649
00:39:37,212 --> 00:39:38,614
All right.

650
00:39:39,915 --> 00:39:43,085
They must buy the land to build a factory.

651
00:39:45,254 --> 00:39:46,488
Hey.

652
00:39:46,488 --> 00:39:49,024
Please say something.

653
00:39:49,024 --> 00:39:50,826
Is what the chief said true?

654
00:39:52,728 --> 00:39:55,864
Since you're all here,
it'll be easier to tell you.

655
00:39:57,433 --> 00:39:59,134
It has been finalized...

656
00:40:00,336 --> 00:40:02,638
that Mat Story's third factory
will be built in Yeonri-ri.

657
00:40:02,638 --> 00:40:03,839
What?

658
00:40:03,839 --> 00:40:05,841
What are you talking about?

659
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:13,382
For smooth progress,

660
00:40:13,382 --> 00:40:15,050
we need your cooperation.

661
00:40:16,618 --> 00:40:17,486
Please...

662
00:40:18,954 --> 00:40:19,989
sell your land.

663
00:40:24,059 --> 00:40:25,094
Mr. Seong.

664
00:40:25,594 --> 00:40:27,563
How can you say such a thing?

665
00:40:28,163 --> 00:40:31,100
We thought of you as family.
How could you do this to us?

666
00:40:32,401 --> 00:40:33,869
Tell us.

667
00:40:34,370 --> 00:40:36,038
Are all these things true?

668
00:40:36,739 --> 00:40:37,940
Selling the land...

669
00:40:38,407 --> 00:40:40,142
isn't a bad thing for you either.

670
00:40:41,076 --> 00:40:42,911
The compensation has been fairly set,

671
00:40:43,812 --> 00:40:44,880
and I'll explain everything one by one...

672
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:46,115
Shut your mouth.

673
00:40:47,149 --> 00:40:48,283
You scumbag.

674
00:40:49,785 --> 00:40:50,653
How dare you.

675
00:40:51,186 --> 00:40:52,454
Why are you doing this?

676
00:40:53,722 --> 00:40:55,457
Even if you respond emotionally,

677
00:40:56,358 --> 00:40:57,726
the outcome won't change.

678
00:40:58,160 --> 00:40:59,762
Unbelievable.

679
00:41:01,397 --> 00:41:02,798
You animal.

680
00:41:08,537 --> 00:41:09,638
How dare you!

681
00:41:15,177 --> 00:41:16,545
I'll come back another time.

682
00:41:18,647 --> 00:41:20,382
Traitor! Don't ever come back.

683
00:41:22,351 --> 00:41:24,153
Get out of our village.

684
00:41:35,230 --> 00:41:36,298
Mom, Dad. You're back.

685
00:41:36,999 --> 00:41:38,667
We'll make you something nutritious.

686
00:41:40,903 --> 00:41:41,770
Dad.

687
00:41:43,272 --> 00:41:44,106
Mom.

688
00:41:46,075 --> 00:41:47,176
Why is Dad like that?

689
00:41:47,876 --> 00:41:49,211
You should go home.

690
00:41:49,678 --> 00:41:50,546
What?

691
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:54,149
Mother. Did I do something wrong?

692
00:41:54,883 --> 00:41:56,085
This is an adult matter.

693
00:41:58,354 --> 00:42:01,023
He's burning with anger today,

694
00:42:01,623 --> 00:42:02,992
and it won't cool down easily.

695
00:42:11,600 --> 00:42:12,735
Mom. Dad.

696
00:42:19,508 --> 00:42:20,943
Honey, you're home.

697
00:42:21,644 --> 00:42:23,212
Honey.

698
00:42:24,213 --> 00:42:26,248
What happened?

699
00:42:26,548 --> 00:42:28,183
What is all this?

700
00:42:30,552 --> 00:42:33,589
There was an incident.

701
00:42:40,262 --> 00:42:42,665
I think something happened
to village chief's family.

702
00:42:44,667 --> 00:42:45,567
What?

703
00:42:46,635 --> 00:42:47,469
Goodness.

704
00:42:49,938 --> 00:42:51,707
This isn't your wrongdoing, is it?

705
00:42:51,707 --> 00:42:52,541
Right?

706
00:43:05,254 --> 00:43:07,790
Please take one and read it.

707
00:43:07,790 --> 00:43:09,692
Please pass it back.

708
00:43:13,195 --> 00:43:15,731
Those who received free fertilizer...

709
00:43:15,731 --> 00:43:19,468
have already been listed as
having agreed to the factory construction.

710
00:43:19,468 --> 00:43:20,369
What?

711
00:43:21,570 --> 00:43:22,438
When?

712
00:43:22,838 --> 00:43:23,706
Those...

713
00:43:24,139 --> 00:43:26,408
who sell their land
during the first acquisition period...

714
00:43:27,509 --> 00:43:30,079
will receive an additional compensation
of $30,000.

715
00:43:30,079 --> 00:43:31,580
$30,000?

716
00:43:32,047 --> 00:43:33,215
Then it's better to sell.

717
00:43:34,249 --> 00:43:37,152
These are the most considerate terms
the company can offer.

718
00:43:37,152 --> 00:43:38,687
Don't miss this opportunity...

719
00:43:38,687 --> 00:43:40,389
and please make a quick decision.

720
00:43:43,525 --> 00:43:45,127
You said it was free fertilizer,

721
00:43:45,127 --> 00:43:47,463
and now you're saying it was
a consent for the factory? How ridiculous.

722
00:43:47,463 --> 00:43:50,432
I only took the fertilizer
because I trusted the village chief.

723
00:43:50,432 --> 00:43:52,434
How could this happen?

724
00:43:52,434 --> 00:43:54,203
Let's be honest here.

725
00:43:54,203 --> 00:43:57,172
Isn't it actually better for us to sell?

726
00:43:57,406 --> 00:43:58,507
What?

727
00:43:58,507 --> 00:44:00,743
Are you saying
you're going to sell your land?

728
00:44:00,743 --> 00:44:04,213
If Mat Story offers a fair price,

729
00:44:04,213 --> 00:44:05,447
I'll sell too.

730
00:44:05,447 --> 00:44:06,482
Exactly.

731
00:44:06,482 --> 00:44:09,051
I should help with my kids' rent.

732
00:44:09,051 --> 00:44:09,818
That's right.

733
00:44:09,818 --> 00:44:11,620
You're going to destroy
the whole village...

734
00:44:11,620 --> 00:44:13,789
over a bit of money?

735
00:44:13,789 --> 00:44:17,159
- Don't be ridiculous!
- We can't sell the land.

736
00:44:19,161 --> 00:44:21,196
Come here.

737
00:44:23,999 --> 00:44:26,535
Stop fighting. This is crazy.

738
00:44:39,815 --> 00:44:40,716
Enough!

739
00:44:43,052 --> 00:44:44,586
This is all my fault.

740
00:44:45,587 --> 00:44:49,258
We've known each other our whole lives.
What are we doing right now?

741
00:44:50,025 --> 00:44:50,726
What?

742
00:44:51,727 --> 00:44:53,395
Ten years ago, because of my incompetence,

743
00:44:53,395 --> 00:44:55,564
I broke your hearts.

744
00:44:56,732 --> 00:44:57,633
This time too...

745
00:44:58,600 --> 00:45:00,035
Even if it costs me everything,

746
00:45:00,703 --> 00:45:03,038
I'll take full responsibility.

747
00:45:04,974 --> 00:45:06,375
Please trust me just this once.

748
00:45:06,375 --> 00:45:07,876
Please trust me...

749
00:45:07,876 --> 00:45:08,944
Ju Hyeong.

750
00:45:09,411 --> 00:45:10,946
Chief.

751
00:45:10,946 --> 00:45:11,880
Chief.

752
00:45:16,185 --> 00:45:17,119
Seong Tae Hun.

753
00:45:21,457 --> 00:45:23,025
Are you really a monster?

754
00:45:23,792 --> 00:45:25,461
There's some misunderstanding...

755
00:45:30,232 --> 00:45:32,534
This isn't something
to handle emotionally.

756
00:45:32,534 --> 00:45:33,636
It's company business.

757
00:45:33,969 --> 00:45:34,970
Company business?

758
00:45:36,171 --> 00:45:38,507
Turning people who've been like brothers
for 30 years against each other...

759
00:45:38,974 --> 00:45:40,743
over a bit of money.

760
00:45:40,743 --> 00:45:41,910
That's company business?

761
00:45:43,646 --> 00:45:45,314
Doing this to them...

762
00:45:46,382 --> 00:45:47,549
Does it put you at ease?

763
00:45:49,485 --> 00:45:51,754
This is the only way.

764
00:45:52,855 --> 00:45:54,990
You should think carefully too.

765
00:45:55,591 --> 00:45:58,293
The company won't stop.

766
00:46:19,181 --> 00:46:20,215
Good work today.

767
00:46:29,958 --> 00:46:30,826
Mr. Jeong.

768
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:33,696
What was this compensation plan based on?

769
00:46:34,797 --> 00:46:37,733
That was directly instructed by Mr. Choi.

770
00:46:38,300 --> 00:46:39,201
Directly?

771
00:46:39,902 --> 00:46:42,237
So the compensation
will definitely be paid as is?

772
00:46:43,605 --> 00:46:44,473
I'm not sure.

773
00:46:45,841 --> 00:46:48,744
I also thought the amount was excessive.

774
00:46:49,712 --> 00:46:52,147
But maybe it's just because they need
to secure the land first.

775
00:46:55,517 --> 00:46:57,486
So it's bait?

776
00:46:59,888 --> 00:47:01,824
I don't know.

777
00:47:02,825 --> 00:47:04,326
I just do what I'm told.

778
00:47:04,960 --> 00:47:08,130
I'll go meet the other residents.

779
00:47:08,697 --> 00:47:09,665
Go ahead.

780
00:47:15,838 --> 00:47:17,539
(Yeonri-ri Land Acquisition
and Farm Support Notice)

781
00:47:25,180 --> 00:47:27,683
How's the land purchasing going?

782
00:47:28,484 --> 00:47:30,119
I was actually just about to call you.

783
00:47:30,119 --> 00:47:32,087
About the first compensation plan.

784
00:47:32,921 --> 00:47:34,823
The amount seems to be set quite high.

785
00:47:35,491 --> 00:47:36,925
Is it okay to proceed like this?

786
00:47:37,426 --> 00:47:38,727
That's...

787
00:47:38,727 --> 00:47:41,697
something to discuss after we get them
to sign the contract.

788
00:47:42,197 --> 00:47:43,432
Don't be so naive.

789
00:47:45,234 --> 00:47:48,871
Are you presenting false conditions
to the residents?

790
00:47:50,105 --> 00:47:52,508
Leave that to Mr. Jeong.

791
00:47:53,609 --> 00:47:56,879
The seedling unsuitability report
we sent earlier.

792
00:47:56,879 --> 00:47:59,048
I called you to see when you will sign it.

793
00:47:59,448 --> 00:48:03,419
One report from you,
former top researcher of Mat Story,

794
00:48:03,419 --> 00:48:06,955
declaring the crops
grown in Yeonri-ri unsuitable...

795
00:48:06,955 --> 00:48:09,191
would finish everything.

796
00:48:11,193 --> 00:48:13,929
You know that better than anyone.

797
00:48:15,030 --> 00:48:16,699
We need to finish
acquiring the land first...

798
00:48:16,699 --> 00:48:18,233
to avoid complications with the paperwork.

799
00:48:19,101 --> 00:48:21,437
I'll complete the land acquisition first,
then handle it.

800
00:48:22,604 --> 00:48:23,505
Goodbye.

801
00:48:59,742 --> 00:49:01,577
What's he doing here?

802
00:49:02,778 --> 00:49:04,113
Unbelievable.

803
00:49:04,613 --> 00:49:06,248
You're late, Ji Cheon.

804
00:49:07,716 --> 00:49:09,585
I wasn't sure if I should come.

805
00:49:10,519 --> 00:49:11,453
Is it okay?

806
00:49:12,287 --> 00:49:13,789
Of course.

807
00:49:13,789 --> 00:49:15,824
Adult matters should be handled by adults.

808
00:49:17,793 --> 00:49:18,761
It's him.

809
00:49:19,294 --> 00:49:20,729
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

810
00:49:20,729 --> 00:49:22,498
He's the son of Mat Story, right?

811
00:49:22,998 --> 00:49:24,033
Let's go.

812
00:49:24,033 --> 00:49:25,534
Where are you going?
At least finish eating first.

813
00:49:27,269 --> 00:49:28,170
Where are you going?

814
00:49:34,143 --> 00:49:35,744
I guess they were done eating.

815
00:49:38,947 --> 00:49:40,182
Bo Mi.

816
00:49:40,182 --> 00:49:41,917
I ran into your mother on the way here.

817
00:49:41,917 --> 00:49:44,019
She asked you to stop by the salon.

818
00:49:44,019 --> 00:49:45,120
My mom?

819
00:49:45,454 --> 00:49:46,922
Why didn't she just call?

820
00:49:47,489 --> 00:49:49,191
I'll be right back, Ji Cheon.

821
00:49:49,191 --> 00:49:49,992
Okay.

822
00:49:56,532 --> 00:49:58,100
Would you like an Americano?

823
00:49:59,101 --> 00:50:01,971
It feels uneasy...

824
00:50:03,472 --> 00:50:06,175
to see everyone including Bo Mi trying
not to make you feel uncomfortable, right?

825
00:50:07,543 --> 00:50:09,478
You weren't exactly welcomed
from the beginning.

826
00:50:10,379 --> 00:50:12,081
What exactly are you trying to say?

827
00:50:12,681 --> 00:50:13,615
Honestly,

828
00:50:14,616 --> 00:50:16,151
the way you are right now looks pathetic.

829
00:50:21,056 --> 00:50:22,057
I know.

830
00:50:23,826 --> 00:50:26,061
Even if I can't do anything right now,

831
00:50:26,695 --> 00:50:28,464
I'll find a way to change things soon.

832
00:50:30,065 --> 00:50:32,768
Until then, I'll keep coming here.

833
00:50:33,802 --> 00:50:34,870
And from now on,

834
00:50:37,306 --> 00:50:38,407
I'll protect Bo Mi.

835
00:50:44,647 --> 00:50:46,548
That mindset is enough.

836
00:50:47,716 --> 00:50:49,852
When you feel like you can't do anything,

837
00:50:50,152 --> 00:50:51,453
just focus on one thing.

838
00:50:52,855 --> 00:50:54,256
See if the person you love...

839
00:50:54,690 --> 00:50:57,092
is crying or smiling.

840
00:51:02,197 --> 00:51:03,132
Good luck.

841
00:51:14,977 --> 00:51:16,912
What was that? My mom said
she never asked for me.

842
00:51:19,214 --> 00:51:20,382
Did Officer Park leave?

843
00:51:21,717 --> 00:51:22,618
Yes.

844
00:51:25,721 --> 00:51:26,789
Just one thing.

845
00:51:49,611 --> 00:51:51,513
Didn't you hear what I said?

846
00:51:52,614 --> 00:51:54,149
Just sell your land, Chief.

847
00:51:54,917 --> 00:51:57,486
Then I won't approach anyone else.

848
00:51:58,854 --> 00:52:01,991
Your land connects to the factory site.

849
00:52:02,524 --> 00:52:03,859
If we secure that,

850
00:52:03,859 --> 00:52:05,594
the company won't...

851
00:52:05,594 --> 00:52:07,196
try to expand any further.

852
00:52:09,598 --> 00:52:11,634
If word gets out that I sold my land,

853
00:52:11,634 --> 00:52:14,370
everyone else will start lining up
to sell too. That's what you're saying?

854
00:52:15,337 --> 00:52:16,405
Wow.

855
00:52:17,439 --> 00:52:19,274
Thinking about exploiting others...

856
00:52:19,274 --> 00:52:22,211
hasn't changed at all, has it?

857
00:52:26,415 --> 00:52:28,550
I guess I should pay the price
for trusting you, right?

858
00:52:30,919 --> 00:52:32,421
Go ahead and buy my land.

859
00:52:33,522 --> 00:52:34,390
In return,

860
00:52:35,691 --> 00:52:38,093
don't you dare go to anyone else
and ask for their land.

861
00:52:38,927 --> 00:52:39,928
You know what?

862
00:52:40,562 --> 00:52:44,233
Every corner of this village
is owned by someone.

863
00:52:45,234 --> 00:52:47,069
You won't be able to do anything
without their permission.

864
00:52:47,936 --> 00:52:49,872
I'll be watching closely...

865
00:52:49,872 --> 00:52:51,340
to see what you do with that land.

866
00:52:52,641 --> 00:52:53,475
You!

867
00:52:53,942 --> 00:52:56,478
Have you lost your mind?

868
00:52:56,478 --> 00:52:58,414
You're selling your land?

869
00:52:58,847 --> 00:53:01,150
What are you, Jesus?

870
00:53:01,617 --> 00:53:03,319
Buddha?

871
00:53:03,319 --> 00:53:07,022
Why do you always carry the cross
all by yourself?

872
00:53:08,691 --> 00:53:10,025
Ten years ago too.

873
00:53:10,392 --> 00:53:12,828
You ran around alone
as the village chief...

874
00:53:12,828 --> 00:53:16,031
and ended up completely heartbroken.

875
00:53:16,031 --> 00:53:18,033
And you're doing it again?

876
00:53:18,434 --> 00:53:20,035
You think becoming a fool alone...

877
00:53:20,436 --> 00:53:22,671
will fix everything?

878
00:53:25,975 --> 00:53:29,678
How do you even bear
to show your face around here?

879
00:53:29,678 --> 00:53:30,546
Leave.

880
00:53:30,813 --> 00:53:33,248
Don't even set foot in our yard.

881
00:53:33,248 --> 00:53:34,216
Just go.

882
00:53:35,351 --> 00:53:36,919
Leave!

883
00:53:37,286 --> 00:53:38,387
Go.

884
00:53:40,356 --> 00:53:41,256
Why you...

885
00:53:42,591 --> 00:53:44,326
- Go!
- What's this?

886
00:53:45,894 --> 00:53:47,096
What's wrong with her?

887
00:53:47,296 --> 00:53:48,364
What's this?

888
00:53:51,100 --> 00:53:53,435
It's salty. It must be sea salt.

889
00:54:04,546 --> 00:54:05,514
Ju Hyeong.

890
00:54:07,383 --> 00:54:09,385
I'm getting too tired now.

891
00:54:11,754 --> 00:54:13,122
Look at our youngest, Mak Rae.

892
00:54:15,290 --> 00:54:17,660
How long can I keep living like this,
working the soil?

893
00:54:18,360 --> 00:54:19,995
It's nice and salty.

894
00:54:22,898 --> 00:54:26,435
All the land is under Mak Rae's name.

895
00:54:27,036 --> 00:54:28,637
We'll sell the land,

896
00:54:28,637 --> 00:54:31,307
get a small apartment downtown,

897
00:54:31,540 --> 00:54:34,810
and the three of us will live together.

898
00:54:35,611 --> 00:54:38,747
We can't farm anymore.

899
00:54:56,231 --> 00:54:57,566
Here's the contract.

900
00:54:57,566 --> 00:54:59,201
Please stamp here.

901
00:54:59,902 --> 00:55:00,869
I'll do it.

902
00:55:03,272 --> 00:55:04,273
I don't have my seal.

903
00:55:05,007 --> 00:55:05,841
Ju Hyeong.

904
00:55:06,375 --> 00:55:07,609
Where's my seal?

905
00:55:10,279 --> 00:55:11,280
What did you do with it?

906
00:55:13,148 --> 00:55:14,817
I'll go bring it.

907
00:55:14,817 --> 00:55:17,152
Just wait here. I'll go find it.

908
00:55:17,720 --> 00:55:18,921
I'll go bring it.

909
00:55:20,622 --> 00:55:21,790
I'm going crazy here.

910
00:55:27,663 --> 00:55:28,564
Dong Sik.

911
00:55:30,532 --> 00:55:32,835
The chief isn't selling his land, is he?

912
00:55:33,936 --> 00:55:35,638
Imagine why he's doing this.

913
00:55:36,972 --> 00:55:39,074
He just couldn't stand...

914
00:55:39,475 --> 00:55:40,576
watching the villagers fight like that.

915
00:55:44,480 --> 00:55:45,881
Tell me.

916
00:55:45,881 --> 00:55:47,750
Why are you so desperate to ruin us?

917
00:55:49,084 --> 00:55:50,519
I'll see you at Mat Story.

918
00:55:50,986 --> 00:55:51,920
Hey!

919
00:55:52,421 --> 00:55:53,422
Seong Tae Hun.

920
00:55:55,190 --> 00:55:56,291
Unbelievable.

921
00:56:04,133 --> 00:56:06,335
I guess he's bent on seeing this through.

922
00:56:07,202 --> 00:56:10,572
I never thought Mr. Seong could do this.

923
00:56:12,741 --> 00:56:13,776
Goodness.

924
00:56:13,776 --> 00:56:14,910
Is the chief all right?

925
00:56:24,320 --> 00:56:25,754
Goodness.

926
00:56:27,389 --> 00:56:29,224
Tell me, you jerk.

927
00:56:29,958 --> 00:56:31,660
Is that all Yeonri-ri means to you?

928
00:56:32,294 --> 00:56:33,996
Is that all I mean to you?

929
00:56:35,731 --> 00:56:37,967
Tell me, you jerk. Tell me what happened.

930
00:56:37,967 --> 00:56:38,867
Yes, Mr. Choi.

931
00:56:40,302 --> 00:56:42,137
The land acquisition is still in progress.

932
00:56:42,705 --> 00:56:43,572
Mr. Seong?

933
00:56:44,506 --> 00:56:47,810
It seems like he's still persuading
the village chief.

934
00:56:48,610 --> 00:56:50,012
You've made a good choice.

935
00:56:50,746 --> 00:56:52,848
Set up the meeting then.

936
00:56:52,848 --> 00:56:54,049
I think he's been persuaded.

937
00:56:54,717 --> 00:56:56,952
The chief is going to sell his land.

938
00:56:58,921 --> 00:56:59,822
All right.

939
00:57:06,061 --> 00:57:08,364
(Yeonri-ri residents strongly oppose
factory construction)

940
00:57:10,566 --> 00:57:12,735
(We are against building a factory
that threatens our livelihood)

941
00:57:12,735 --> 00:57:15,337
(Shameless Mat Story, leave our home)

942
00:57:15,337 --> 00:57:17,706
(Mat Story)

943
00:57:19,942 --> 00:57:22,544
You'll be building a factory on my land.

944
00:57:23,379 --> 00:57:26,248
So I figured I should come
see your faces myself.

945
00:57:26,815 --> 00:57:28,050
So here I am.

946
00:57:28,384 --> 00:57:30,085
You've made a wise decision, Chief.

947
00:57:30,886 --> 00:57:32,821
In the end, all that remains
is trust, right?

948
00:57:33,656 --> 00:57:35,457
You'll only hurt yourself if you resist.

949
00:57:36,659 --> 00:57:39,294
You're sitting here in your nice office,

950
00:57:39,294 --> 00:57:42,331
scheming how to suck the life
out of other people.

951
00:57:45,334 --> 00:57:47,469
I just need to sign my name here, right?

952
00:57:49,505 --> 00:57:50,539
Please sign here.

953
00:57:51,607 --> 00:57:53,876
Once you make the move,

954
00:57:53,876 --> 00:57:56,779
persuading the villagers
will only be a matter of time.

955
00:57:56,779 --> 00:57:59,381
We'll make sure you're well taken care of.

956
00:58:19,902 --> 00:58:23,572
We've set aside $300,000...

957
00:58:26,008 --> 00:58:27,376
as an incentive for you,
including the land.

958
00:58:30,279 --> 00:58:33,682
This is well above the market value.

959
00:58:40,089 --> 00:58:42,257
Cash, of course.

960
00:58:42,658 --> 00:58:44,259
We can't leave a trace.

961
00:58:44,259 --> 00:58:45,794
It'll be clean and simple for both sides.

962
00:58:46,261 --> 00:58:47,429
And you know, right?

963
00:58:47,896 --> 00:58:49,064
There's a fee.

964
00:58:50,232 --> 00:58:51,166
Thirty percent.

965
00:59:24,733 --> 00:59:26,535
It's done.

966
00:59:28,304 --> 00:59:29,238
Okay.

967
00:59:35,811 --> 00:59:37,279
It's over.

968
00:59:53,829 --> 00:59:54,663
Mr. Seong.

969
00:59:57,566 --> 00:59:59,702
It's over.

970
01:00:05,274 --> 01:00:06,508
What are you two up to?

971
01:00:07,609 --> 01:00:09,111
Sell the land of Yeonri-ri to you?

972
01:00:13,782 --> 01:00:16,618
We wouldn't sell you
even a worthless scrap.

973
01:00:25,894 --> 01:00:27,196
(You think it'll work)

974
01:00:27,196 --> 01:00:28,364
You think it'll work?

975
01:00:28,664 --> 01:00:29,631
Unbelievable.

976
01:00:34,770 --> 01:00:35,704
When they're standing...

977
01:00:36,472 --> 01:00:38,974
at the edge of a cliff,
where they can neither live or die,

978
01:00:41,543 --> 01:00:44,413
people usually think about falling.

979
01:00:47,282 --> 01:00:48,217
But...

980
01:00:49,318 --> 01:00:50,486
a true farmer...

981
01:00:52,354 --> 01:00:54,423
plants roots in the cracks of that cliff,

982
01:00:57,359 --> 01:00:58,560
breaks through the wall,

983
01:01:00,462 --> 01:01:01,630
and finds...

984
01:01:02,731 --> 01:01:03,732
a third path.

985
01:01:33,262 --> 01:01:36,265
(Cabbage Your Life)

986
01:01:36,265 --> 01:01:37,032
(Epilogue)

987
01:01:37,032 --> 01:01:38,701
If my dad finds out
we're meeting like this,

988
01:01:38,701 --> 01:01:40,169
he'll rip all your hair out, Ji Cheon.

989
01:01:40,169 --> 01:01:41,904
- He'll rip my hair out?
- Yes.

990
01:01:42,705 --> 01:01:43,639
That's not good.

991
01:01:50,446 --> 01:01:51,413
Bye.

992
01:01:51,413 --> 01:01:52,214
Bye.

993
01:02:06,862 --> 01:02:08,063
I guess I won't lose my hair.

994
01:02:08,797 --> 01:02:10,799
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

